    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1797914887" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1797914887" />
    <a title="The Girl Murdered by Her TBR" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/53967892-the-girl-murdered-by-her-tbr"><img alt="The Girl Murdered by Her TBR" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1633144540p2/53967892.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1797914887?book_show_action=true">Feb 01, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="The Girl Murdered by Her TBR" class="user" itemprop="url" name="The Girl Murdered by Her TBR" href="/user/show/53967892-the-girl-murdered-by-her-tbr">The Girl Murdered by Her TBR</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/53967892-the-girl-murdered-by-her-tbr?shelf=owned-books">owned-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/53967892-the-girl-murdered-by-her-tbr?shelf=part-of-a-series">part-of-a-series</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/53967892-the-girl-murdered-by-her-tbr?shelf=young-adult">young-adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/53967892-the-girl-murdered-by-her-tbr?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1797914887" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8854971133426608546"><b>3.75 stars!!!!</b><br/><br/><b>FULL REVIEW</b><br/><br/>I was really excited to read another work of Rick Riordan. I read the PJO a long time ago and I absolutely loved it. <br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1517932534ra/25013911.gif' width='350' height='300' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>This though? Not so much. <br/><br/>I liked it. The humor and the characters are interesting. What exactly is my problem with it? The slow paced plot. It was boring and just so freaking slooow.<br/><br/>Don&apos;t get me wrong. I was still amazed how Riordan retold the Norse Mythology. His creativeness is phenomenal and one of a kind. The way he retells a story and add his own kin</span>
  <span id="freeText8854971133426608546" style="display:none"><b>3.75 stars!!!!</b><br><br><b>FULL REVIEW</b><br><br>I was really excited to read another work of Rick Riordan. I read the PJO a long time ago and I absolutely loved it. <br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1517932534ra/25013911.gif" width="350" height="300" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>This though? Not so much. <br><br>I liked it. The humor and the characters are interesting. What exactly is my problem with it? The slow paced plot. It was boring and just so freaking slooow.<br><br>Don't get me wrong. I was still amazed how Riordan retold the Norse Mythology. His creativeness is phenomenal and one of a kind. The way he retells a story and add his own kind of style is fantastic. I really don't know why this book didn't work out for me. Maybe I expected a lot from it. <br><br>But I do love some parts of this book. I love the world building, it was so magical and astonishingly perfect. Rick Riordan once again managed to reinvent things and distort reality with his awesome storytelling skills. This book's hilarious dialogues also was one of the reason why I like this book. And of course, Magnus's dorky and sassy personality. Not to mention he really looks like Kurt Cobain!!! <br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1518668384ra/25062656.gif" width="350" height="300" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"> <br><br>His resemblance to Kurt made me swoon the entire time. Kurt is one of my ultimate crushes so yeah... Swoon. Read. Swoon. <br><br>I also found the gods really hilarious! I’m pretty sure my usual perspective with Thor, Odin, and the rest of the norse gods will never be the same again. Rick Riordan managed “again” to make me laugh dozen of times while reading his work. I really can't get over with Thor's personality in this book. I. JUST. CAN'T. <br><br>I'll definitely continue reading this series soon-ish... Hopefully this 2018? Who knows?</span>
  <a data-text-id="8854971133426608546" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


