      <div class=" clearFloats bigBox"><div class="h2Container gradientHeaderContainer"><h2 class="brownBackground"><a href="/work/quotes/21400019-the-sword-of-summer">Quotes from The Sword of Summer</a></h2></div><div class="bigBoxBody"><div class="bigBoxContent containerWithHeaderContent">
          <div class="stacked" tyle="padding-bottom:15px">
            <span class="readable">&ldquo;Myths are simply stories about truths we've forgotten.&rdquo;</span>
            <nobr>
              &mdash;
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/quotes/7296058-myths-are-simply-stories-about-truths-we-ve-forgotten">316 likes</a>
            </nobr>
            <div class="clear"></div>
          </div>
          <div class="stacked" tyle="padding-bottom:15px">
            <span class="readable">&ldquo;Could you do a glamour and turn into something smaller?" I asked it. "Preferably not a chain, since it's no longer the 1990s?"<br /><br />The sword didn't reply (duh), but I imagined it was humming at a more interrogative pitch, like, Such as what?<br /><br />"I dunno. Something pocket-size and innocuous. A pen, maybe?"<br /><br />The sword pulsed, almost like it was laughing. I imagined it saying, A pen sword. That is the stupidest thing I've ever heard.&rdquo;</span>
            <nobr>
              &mdash;
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/quotes/7295309-could-you-do-a-glamour-and-turn-into-something-smaller">299 likes</a>
            </nobr>
